SUMMARY: “Ain’t No Sunshine …” Photography Exhibition
DESCRIPTION:Local photographer and Pillar Arts member Rodney Margison wil
 l present his second solo exhibition\, “Ain’t No Sunshine …\,” from Febru
 ary 6–28\, 2026\, at Backspace Gallery in Bloomington\, Indiana. A public
  reception will take place Friday\, February 6\, from 5–8 p.m. as part of
  the Bloomington Gallery Walk. (Photos from this exhibition will not be a
 vailable for purchase.)\n\nThe exhibition\, made possible by a City of Bl
 oomington Arts Commission 2024 Artistic Advancement Grant\, shows 34 phot
 ographs captured in the hours leading up to and in the days and months fo
 llowing the February 2017 death of his wife’s mother to leukemia and kidn
 ey cancer. Made in a documentary style\, the images capture a bittersweet
  celebration—a slumber party to mark her birthday three months early. And
  by the end of that weekend\, she was gone.\n\nMargison’s photos were mad
 e with the full knowledge\, cooperation\, and support of his mother-in-la
 w and her family.\n\nPresented chronologically\, “Ain’t No Sunshine …” re
 flects the impact one person’s life has on a community of family and frie
 nds\, the joy of love\, the reality and permanence of death\, and the ong
 oing process of grief.\n\nAbout Rodney Margison:\n\nRodney Margison is a 
 multi-award-winning professional photographer based in Bloomington\, Indi
 ana. His photography is a fixture in south-central Indiana’s creative com
 munity\, spanning genres and blending lines between documentary and fine 
 art. From 2003–2009 he was the staff photographer for the “Brown County D
 emocrat” newspaper in Nashville\, Indiana\, before co-founding one of the
  area’s first online news sites\, “This Is Brown http://County.com.” In 2
 016 he joined Bloomington’s culture and lifestyle magazine\, “Bloom\,” as
  associate editor\, and has been its managing editor and photo editor sin
 ce 2020. His work has been accepted into nearly two dozen group art and p
 hotography exhibitions and earned several awards. “Ain’t No Sunshine …’ i
 s his second solo exhibition\, following “A Little Extra Love\,” which ra
 n during October 2025 at Bloomington’s Fountain Square. Margison received
  a 2024 City of Bloomington Arts Commission Artistic Advancement Grant an
 d is a member of the Bloomington Photography Club\, Pillar Arts\, and the
  Society of Professional Journalists. See his work and learn more at http
 ://rodneymargison.com\n\nAbout Backspace Gallery:\n\nBackspace Gallery\, 
 inside Bonne Fête at 112 W. 6th St. in Bloomington\, Indiana\, was founde
 d in 2022 and is dedicated to showcasing thought-provoking and beautiful 
 works of art in a variety of mediums by local\, regional\, and national a
 rtists. It is open Monday–Saturday\, 11 a.m.–7 p.m.\, and noon–5 p.m. on 
 Sunday. Visit http://backspacegallery.com or find them on Facebook to lea
 rn more.\n\n
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Exhibition
