SUMMARY: Tri Kappa Exhibition Reception
DESCRIPTION:Tri Kappa 125th Anniversary\n\nOpening Exhibition Reception\n
 \nBrown County Art Guild\n\nFebruary 22\, 2026\n\n2-4pm / Remarks at 3pm\
 n\nCelebrate 125 years of Tri Kappa at the opening reception of a special
  exhibition drawn from the Tri Kappa Art Collection. Featuring works by I
 ndiana artists\, this exhibition honors Tri-Kappa’s long-standing commitm
 ent to the arts. Join us in celebrating the exhibition and Tri Kappa’s hi
 storic anniversary. Light refreshments will be served.\n\nFree & open to 
 the public.\n\n----------------------------------------------------------
 ------------------\n\nTri Kappa 125th Anniversary Exhibition\n\nFebruary 
 22 – June 26\, 2026\n\nBrown County Art Guild\n\nJoin us in celebrating 1
 25 years of Tri Kappa and its rich art collection.\nSince its inception i
 n 1901\, Tri Kappa has served as a cornerstone of Indiana’s cultural land
 scape\, fostering a legacy of charity\, culture\, and education that span
 s generations. The Guild will showcase a curated selection of paintings f
 rom the Tri-Kappa collection\, highlighting the talents of Indiana artist
 s\, past and present. Discover works that reflect the beauty\, creativity
 \, and enduring spirit of our state’s artistic heritage.\n\n-------------
 -----------------------------------------------------------\n\nBrown Coun
 ty Art Guild – A not for profit organization located in the heart of down
 town Nashville\, Indiana. On display throughout its galleries is a prized
  collection of historic paintings as well as current works for sale from 
 regional award-winning member artists. The Guild also offers artist demon
 strations\, workshops\, and a variety of events or programs throughout th
 e year.\n\nWinter Hours - January & February 2026\, Monday-Wednesday clos
 ed or by appt.~ Thursday-Saturday\, 11am-5pm ~ Sunday\, 12-4pm\n\nMarch –
  December 2026\, Monday – Saturday 11am-5pm & Sundays 12-4pm
