SUMMARY: John McEnroe: In the Realm of Perfection w/ Q&A | Cinematic Spor
 ts Documentary: History\, Politics\, Aesthetics
DESCRIPTION:Julien Faraut’s John McEnroe: In the Realm of Perfection expl
 ores the tennis legend’s psyche and emotion on the court of the 1984 Fren
 ch Open. Through 16mm film\, Faraut reimagines athletic performance as ci
 nematic and aesthetic performance\, blurring the boundaries between these
  two seemingly separate categories. McEnroe’s obsession and volatility ar
 e transformed into an aesthetic consideration of performance and emotion 
 in one of the contemporary period’s most inventive sport documentaries. [
 95 min\; documentary\; English and French with English subtitles]\n\nA Q&
 A will follow the screening.
CATEGORIES:Free
