SUMMARY: Cendrillon
DESCRIPTION:Join the Jacobs School of Music for an evening filled with tr
 ue love and magic on March 6th and 7th in their production of Jules Masse
 net's Cendrillon.\n\nIn contrast with Rossini’s version\, the glass slipp
 er is back in this French grand opera rendition of one of the most belove
 d fairy tales\, based on Charles Perrault’s Cinderella. Here\, Massenet l
 ets us see a daughter’s immense grief—at the loss of her mother\, their h
 ome\, and her place in the family after her father’s remarriage. Yet her 
 remarkable ability to not only survive but to forgive allows her to ultim
 ately triumph. Who can resist the desire to believe that dreams really ca
 n come true and to cheer for our heroine as she overcomes the abuse of he
 r stepfamily to find her soulmate? (And who couldn’t use a Fairy Godmothe
 r?)
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,In-Person,Theatre,Music
