SUMMARY: Saving the Hoosier: The Concert
DESCRIPTION:Join us for SAVING THE HOOSIER: THE CONCERT and connect with 
 people who care about the future of OUR Hoosier National Forest while you
  enjoy live music up close. The live concert will feature Hoosier musicia
 ns Sarah Flint and Jeff Shew\, and is a fundraiser to help complete the n
 ew documentary film “Saving the Hoosier: The Fight for America’s Forests”
 . You will get to see a sneak peek of scenes from the film and meet narra
 tor Hud Mellencamp! There will also be a brief talkback with cast members
  following the sneak peek.\n\nWhile there\, enjoy some food and the oppor
 tunity to bid on locally-made and donated auction items. The film is bein
 g produced by Bloomington-based Women with Guts Productions. There will a
 lso be a brief talkback with members of the cast following the screening.
 \n\nWith Artists for Climate Awareness as fiscal sponsor for the film\, a
 ll donations are tax-deductible. Tickets for the concert are $30\, and in
 clude beverages and pizza\, generously donated by Pizza X. Audience membe
 rs will be invited to participate in a sing-along of the Indiana state so
 ng\, "On the Banks of the Wabash"' that will be used in the film. There w
 ill also be a brief talkback with cast members following the sneak peek.\
 n\n"Saving the Hoosier" follows environmental activists who\, through gra
 ssroots education and lawsuits\, have successfully protected the Hoosier 
 National Forest from the US Forest Service’s plans for commercial logging
  and prescribed burns to benefit timber sales.\n\nFor tickets\, please vi
 sit: https://savingthehoosier.eventbrite.com/ https://savingthehoosier.ev
 entbrite.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExZkhMUERTV1liclZ5S25Id3NydG
