SUMMARY: 2026 State of the City
DESCRIPTION:Mayor Kerry Thomson will take the stage for Bloomington’s 202
 6 State of the City\, an evening dedicated to where we’ve been\, where we
 ’re headed\, and how we move forward together.\n\n\nThis free\, public ev
 ent invites residents\, businesses\, and community partners to gather dow
 ntown for a shared look at Bloomington’s progress and priorities. Doors o
 pen at 5:30 p.m.\, with the program beginning at 6 p.m.\, followed by a r
 eception to connect with neighbors and city leadership.\n\n\nThis year’s 
 State of the City will spotlight the big-picture work shaping Bloomington
  right now—from housing and public safety to economic vitality\, infrastr
 ucture\, transparency\, and long-term financial stewardship. Mayor Thomso
 n will reflect on milestones from the past year and outline the path ahea
 d for a city that continues to serve with intention\, creativity\, and ca
 re.\n\n\nCan’t attend in person? The event will be livestreamed and avail
 able for later viewing through Community Access Television Services (CATS
 ) on local cable and at http://catstv.net https://catstv.net/ catstv.net.
 \n\n\nWe hope you’ll join us.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Free,In-Person,Online
