SUMMARY: Asianfest 2026
DESCRIPTION:AsianFest 2026 – Mosaic Traditions: Piecing a Common Ground\n
 \nAsianFest 2026 is a celebration of the shared histories and diverse her
 itages of Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) communities\, within
  Indiana University and the broader Bloomington community. The event high
 lights the richness and diversity through cultural expression\, storytell
 ing\, and artistic performance. Guided by this year’s theme\, we invite a
 ll attendees to reflect\, connect\, and find peace on common ground.\n\n\
 nTaking place on April 11\, 2026 and organized by the Asian Culture Cente
 r at Indiana University (ACC)\, the event brings together AAPI communitie
 s from across Indiana University and the wider Bloomington area.\n\n\nThe
  program features cultural and informational tabling from 4:00–6:00 PM in
 side the Buskirk-Chumley Theater (BCT) venue\, followed by a staged progr
 am from 7:00–8:30 PM that includes video screenings and live performances
  showcasing AAPI voices and traditions.\n\nThe events and programs within
  AsianFest 2026 are open to all members of Indiana University and the wid
 er Bloomington community. We welcome everyone regardless of age\, cultura
 l affinity\, background\, or identity.\n\n\nThis event is FREE! No ticket
 s are needed for entry.
CATEGORIES:Bloomington,Free,In-Person,Media
