SUMMARY: Finn: A New Musical- At the PB&J Cafe
DESCRIPTION:Constellation Stage & Screen presents “Finn: A New Musical- A
 t the PB&J Cafe\,” on stage May 1-17 at the Waldron Auditorium.\n\nFrom t
 he creator of Doc McStuffins and Vampirina\, Finn is a heartwarming music
 al adventure about a young shark on the brink of growing up. As he prepar
 es to join the fearsome Shark Guard\, Finn can’t shake the feeling that h
 e’s different from the other sharks. Deep inside\, he discovers a colorfu
 l fish inside him—a part of himself that longs to sparkle\, sing\, and da
 nce. As Finn embarks on a journey of self-discovery\, friendship\, and ad
 venture\, he finds the courage to be himself! Fun for all ages!\n\nPB&J C
 afe: A Dinner Theater for Kids! At the PB&J Cafe\, young theatergoers wil
 l enjoy a meal during the performance and leave with autographs from thei
 r favorite characters.\n\n\nSee Constellation’s website for more informat
 ion\, including a detailed performance schedule. Learn more and find tick
 ets at seeconstellation.org/kids/finn/ https://seeconstellation.org/kids/
 finn/ https://seeconstellation.org/kids/finn/
CATEGORIES:
